// The byte literal implicit (spec 5.10: an int literal in 0..=255 is
// assignable to byte) composes with option widening: a `byte?` parameter
// accepts a bare in-range literal directly, not just `none` or an
// explicit `byte(...)` conversion. Checker::expects unwraps one level of
// Opt before the literal check so this falls out of the same chokepoint
// every other byte-implicit site routes through (task-9 review, MINOR 5).
fn take(b byte?) bool {
    return b != none
}

fn main() {
    print(take(5))       // true: literal widens into byte?
    print(take(none))    // false
}
